-- Santander raises stake in Brazil unit to 88.3 pct 
-- By Sarah White
-- Fri Oct 31, 2014 04:05AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Oct 31 (Reuters) - Spain's Santander <SAN.MC> said on Friday its offer to buy out minority shareholders in its Brazilian unit Santander Brasil <SANB4.SA> had been accepted by investors representing 13.65 percent of the subsidiary's capital, bringing the parent group's ownership to 88.3 percent.

